# Polish — Log Structure

## 11. Add day stamp to log entries

**File:** `ui.jsx` or log renderer + all engine files
**Lines:** ~15

**Purpose:** Each log entry shows the day number right-aligned.

### Encoding
- [ ] When pushing to log, prefix with day: `"[42] Arrived at Havana."`
- [ ] Update all `log.push(...)` calls to include `[${state.day}] ` prefix.

### Display
- [ ] In `LogList`, parse prefix and show right-aligned:
  ```jsx
  const dayMatch = entry.match(/^\[(\d+)\]\s*(.*)/);
  if (dayMatch) {
    return (
      <div style={{ display: "flex", justifyContent: "space-between" }}>
        <span>{dayMatch[2]}</span>
        <span style={{ color: T.textFaint, fontSize: 9 }}>Day {dayMatch[1]}</span>
      </div>
    );
  }
  ```
- [ ] Only show day stamp when day number changes from previous entry.

### Acceptance criteria
- [ ] Day stamps are subtle and right-aligned.
- [ ] Day only shown on first entry of each new day.
- [ ] Old saves with day-less entries still render.

